* ETMOYA

** INFO:

**** *Short Description*:
     Largest city in all of Morrodel and Altaria, in structure and population.
     It is the Capital City of Morrodel.
    
**** *Archlord*:
     The Archlord of Etmoya is Aeric, and he came to power recently.
     He has been expanding the city on multiple fronts, improving the farming system and
     importing better soil, building up the city and reinforcing defenses, and building
     up a large and well- trained army. Aeric has ambitions to conquer the other
     province of Maldrell and overthrow King Ayalem.
     
**** *Location*:
     Etmoya resides far to the north, in Morrodel Province.

** City History:
   The City of Etmoya resides much farther north compared to most other
   cities in Morrodel due to the historical roots of the Dur Aldia
   presence. The city was historically a Dur Aldian city that now lies in ruins.\\
   The city was initially a colony city/research project, to research the existing
   Aqueduct system put in place by the ancient Durmains (Dur Aldia branch).\\
   After a century, the Aqueduct system was succesfully harnessed into a farming
   system and drinking supply system.
   A new city was built on top of the existing ruins and foundation, and it quickly
   become a center for progress and immigration, the new farming opportunitys proved
   tempting to many peasants from Maldrell, since land was expenisive in Maldrell and
   the bureacracy and taxation made it difficult to live in Maldrell.\\
   After a few generations, The city quickly rose to a high population and eventually
   boasted its own miltary. The progress however reached a halt, as the rate
   of immigration was too fast for the city to catch up. The city entered a short
   period of uncertatinty and even food shortages. \\
   But, during this critical time, a new Archlord rose to power after the old one died,
   the new Archlord, Archlord Aeric, focused efforts on restoring the city's glory, and
   was immensely successful. Archlord Aeric aggressivley expanded the city, improving
   the farming system, extending the city borders to another layer to add more room
   for immigrants and population growth, and reinforced the cities defenses. He
   also built up the military and reformed it using his skills and knowdegle as a
   general/Archlord, turning the Etmoyan military into one of the most impressive
   in the entire Kingdom, if not the most powerful.
   
   Currently, it is the most technologically advanced city in Altaria, as well as the most
   prosperous, most populated, and arugably powerful with it's fast growing military,
   despite the fact that the city is so far north. It otherwise wouldn't be so prosperous
   but the impressive technology makes it an extrememly prosperous place. \\
   Also known as the "City of Flowing Water", it gets its nickname from the complicated
   filtering waterway systems that flow throughout the city, fed by the technologically
   impressive Durmian Aqueducts. \\
   The Aqueducts bring water from the mountain reservoirs and use it for many purposes
   such as: Drinking water, watering the crops, mills, other power sources, etc.
   Beyond the city walls, the water system branches out to water the vast fields of crops,
   an irrgation system powered by gravity and water pressure that can be controlled from
   within the city.

   However, the strength and prosperity imposes a threat to the other province of
   Maldrell. \\
   Orginally, the province of Morrodel was near uninhabited 300 years ago, but now
   has grown to a massive size becuase of Etmoya. \\
   So naturally, The people of Morrodel wanted independece circa 90 years ago, which was
   granted to them since at the time they were not a threat. \\
   Currently however, the King of Altaria is having a hard time exerting control over
   Morrodel, and with the recent growth of the Etmoyan army, the two provinces are on the
   brink of a civil war between each other.
